In all seriousness though, enchanters are doing what they're supposed to be doing.  Charm the giants and send them in.  Unfortunately, thanks to the goofy pet agro bug, the Giants end up doing the tanking.  Once the pet agro bug is fixed, using charmed pets to help fight will be a valid (non-exploit) tactic.  The AOW won't concentrate on the pets 99% of the time and the tactic won't be "heal the pets for their 32k hp tank health"<br>
<br>
<br>
The tactic of charming pets to help fight is a good tactic.  The tactic of charming a giant to be your main tank with 32k hp that can be Chealed easilly, is an exploit (although I doubt the guilds realized that and that's why VI isn't busting their chops, especially considering how badly VI flubbed the whole conquest ordeal)  The only problem is, like I said above, is that VI will fix the bug, but won't turn on charm again (they'll put it on their to-do list, we know how that is).<br>
<br>
<br>
Disagree with me all you want, I don't side with VI often, but I see VI's point in this.  If your whole tactic of bringing down a supermonster relies on a tanking charmed pet as your main tank, then something is wrong and needs to be fixed. <p><p><a href="http://www.eqdivine.net"><img src="http://members.theglobe.com/FEBertoxx/DRAGONRARA.GIF" width="311" height="184"></a></p>
