I really loved the part where they said that everyone knew the bug still existed in part. That was rich. Like everyone knew, but only this naughty 60 people across all the servers tried to use it. Maybe the rest of us were stupid enough to believe that they had in fact FIXED the bug when they said they did. </I><br>
<br>
Don't hang out with many magicians, do you?  Several Magicians in my guild have been complaining like crazy, and they crack jokes at the fact that their super Jabobar has been able to consistently outtaunt our Main Assist 60 Warrior swinging uber weapons.  Either way, claiming ignorance does not allow you immunity to cheating (even if it is unintentional). Even though VI does act stupid in situations like this, as said above, VI is handling this situation very well, by not punishing the people who dropped the AOW using charmed giants as main tanks, but instead disabled the charmed Giants until a fix can be made to their agro code.<br>
<br>
BTW, seeing Absor's latest posts on the dev board, he's saying that charm will be put back in once the pet agro is fixed.  Once the pet agro is fixed, people will once again be able to attempt the AOW with charmed Giants.  Lets see what happens then.<br>
